This is one of those that I wrote a while back and left in my sandbox. But it was one that got some better responses, so I dusted it off, tweaked it up a bit, and posted it.

The idea here is that you can't know which version is more accurate. The researcher in the second one, Dr. Carter, is supposed to be a generally jaded sort of fellow, used to examining dark eldritch horrors all day, and he's excited to find something that's anomalous butpleasant. But the Foundation isn't in the practice of just accepting the idea that an SCP can be beneficial (since they usually aren't, even when they seem to be). So I leave it up to you to decide which version you think is the truth.







